missionEventData.data2: The Empire is in the throes of defeat and the New Republic is pushing its advantage. But on a far flung world, the Empire discovers a cache of secret weapons. A squadron of Tie Phantoms. Hard to see with the eye and undetectable by Rebel radar these ships are an engineering marvel. Desperate for any advantage against the Rebels, Imperial Director, Ysanne Isard, has ordered the craft into immediate service. But will they be enough to push back the unstoppable Rebel advance?

missionEventData.data1: Well done! All E-Wings have been destroyed.
This is Captain Graves of the Repulse. Director Isard has already selected a new target. Prepare to embark.
Okay. There they are. Remember as soon as we fire our lasers they'll know they we're here. So stay low in the asteroid field and wait for my mark.

Recently we discovered a group of prototype Tie Phantoms at a hidden imperial research facility. Before Endor we had little use for them. The Empire maintained its strength through visible power. But now Director Isard has ordered a test of the fighter. We're going to strike at a squadron of the rebellion's new E-Wings who are patrolling the border regions between Rebel and Imperial space. Once there we're going to keep low in the asteroids until we're within half a klick of the squadron. Then we attack. Remember, we need to keep the existence of the fighter secret, so don't leave any survivors.
The director wants you to make a pass of Lusankya's bridge before you depart.
Okay Alpha squadron you're cleared for departure. Head to the next waypoint and prepare to jump.
Okay, Alpha Squadron. We can't leave any witnesses. Take out that Corvette before they jump!
Well done Alpha Squadron. Corvette destroyed.
Alright Alpha squadron. Sending you the jump coordinates. See you on the other side.

missionEventData.data3: The Director was impressed with your display today and wants to move swiftly to help secure our new borders. Get some food and then get some rest because we’re about to move out again…
